<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="49" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="50.[191,1440,985,1046]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,291,986,1012]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Ecology.</emphasis>
Lowland, montane. Dry forests (beech). Shaded ground; dry soil. Nocturnal; hides during the day under stones and in leaf litter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[192,1441,1063,1124]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,288,1063,1089]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Biology.</emphasis>
Seasonality: October, December, February, August. Tenerals: March. Predacious (based on mouthpart morphology).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[192,915,1141,1168]" box="[192,915,1141,1168]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,387,1141,1167]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Dispersal power.</emphasis>
Subapterous (incapable of flight). Swift runner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[192,804,1185,1212]" box="[192,804,1185,1212]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,454,1185,1211]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Collecting techniques.</emphasis>
Lifting stones; sifting leaf litter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[192,1442,1230,1390]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,303,1230,1256]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is named the Kaikoura region (KA) which includes the 
<typeStatus box="[1093,1141,1230,1256]" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
locality Puhi Puhi Valley, and is applied as a noun in apposition. In addition to diagnostic characters of the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Larochelle &amp; Lariviere" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ctenognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaikoura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Ctenognathus kaikoura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has meso- and metatarsomeres 1–4 without dorsal carinae, characters that separate it from other South Island 
<taxonomicName box="[266,510,1331,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ctenognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[266,418,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Ctenognathus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Larochelle &amp; Lariviere" authorityYear="2021" box="[515,770,1331,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Ctenognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaikoura">
<emphasis box="[515,770,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="49">Ctenognathus kaikoura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the dry beech forests of northeastern areas of the South Island (MB, KA).
</paragraph>
